## VI, 79. Charm for procuring increase of grain.

1\. May this bounteous Nabhasaspati (the lord of the cloud) preserve for
us (possessions) without measure in our house!  
2. Do thou, O Nabhasaspati, keep strengthening food in our house, may
prosperity and goods come hither!  
3. O bounteous god, thou dost command thousandfold prosperity: of that
do thou bestow upon iis, of that do thou give us, in that may we share
with thee!

